<div id="outline-container-orgf3a4f59" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgf3a4f59">Geometry by Vector methods</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgf3a4f59">
<p>
In this section we will learn
</p>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org8e73d81" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org8e73d81">Vectors in R<sup>n</sup></h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org8e73d81">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>The definition of R<sup>n</sup> as a vector space.</li>
<li>A geometric interpretation of addition and multiplication by scalar.</li>
<li>The canonical basis</li>
<li>The change of basis</li>
<li>The Euclidean norm</li>
<li>The Euclidean distance</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org259583f" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org259583f">Dot and cross product</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org259583f">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>The Euclidean inner (dot) product.</li>
<li>The geometrical interpretation of the inner product.</li>
<li>The definition of the vector (cross) product in R<sup>3</sup>.</li>
<li>The geometrical interpretation of v &times; w and |v &times; w| in R<sup>3</sup></li>
<li>Properties of dot and cross product.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org3396110" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org3396110">Lines and planes.</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org3396110">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>The line segment between to vectors in R<sup>n</sup></li>
<li>The equation of a straight line in R<sup>n</sup></li>
<li>The equation of k-planes in R<sup>n</sup>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org9d14b5b" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org9d14b5b">Maps from  R<sup>n</sup> to R<sup>m</sup>,</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org9d14b5b">
<p>
In this section we go from the standard topology of R<sup>n</sup> to partial derivatives.
The aim is to have a collection of tools and theorems that will help us with computations
that will be used in the following sections. As a revision we will introduce:
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Definition of a topological space (X,&tau;)</li>
<li>Open sets in R<sup>n</sup></li>
<li>Close sets in R<sup>n</sup></li>
<li>Compact sets in R<sup>n</sup></li>
<li>Bounded sets in R<sup>n</sup></li>
<li>Heine- Borel theorem</li>
<li>Functions (maps) between Euclidean spaces</li>
<li>Injectivity</li>
<li>Surjectivity</li>
<li>Composition</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org5fac74b" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org5fac74b">Limits</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org5fac74b">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Sequences and convergence.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgd1c127d" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgd1c127d">Continuity</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgd1c127d">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Definition of Continuity.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgd53e526" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgd53e526">Derivative as a linear transformation</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgd53e526">
<ul class="org-ul">
