<div id="outline-container-org605950b" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org605950b">Parameterised curves</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org605950b">
<p>
In this section we will restrict to the study of maps \(\alpha : I \to \mathbb{R}^3\) called curves.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Definition of a parameterised smooth curve.</li>
<li>Definition of a regular curve.</li>
<li>Arch-length</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgc7485d2" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgc7485d2">Local properties of curves</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgc7485d2">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Definition of a curve parameterised by arch-length</li>
<li>Curvature</li>
<li>Torsion</li>
<li>Binormal</li>
<li>Frenet–Serret frame and formulas</li>
<li>Fundamental theorem of the Local Theory of Curves</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org38542a7" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org38542a7">Global properties of curves.</h3>
